**61. Rotate List**

##### **APPROACH -**
* **Take last k nodes from the end and put them at the front**

*First calculate the length of the linked list
Update **k = k % len** for optimization
Create `slow` and `fast` pointers
Iterate to make **fast point to the last node**  and **slow to (k+1)th node from end**
Form the required new pointer links*
</br>

##### **COMPLEXITY -**
* **Time Complexity : O(N)**, where N = number of nodes in the list
* **Space Complexity : O(1)**
</br>

##### **CODE -**

**C++**
```
class Solution {
    inline int getLength(ListNode* head) {
        int len = 0;
        while(head) {
            len++;
            head = head->next;
        }
        return len;
    }
public:
    ListNode* rotateRight(ListNode* head, int k) {
        if(!head)   return head;

        // calculate length and update k
        int len = getLength(head);
        k = k % len;

        // get the required nodes
        ListNode *fast = head, *slow = head;
        while(k--)
            fast = fast->next;
        while(fast->next) {
            slow = slow->next;
            fast = fast->next;
        }

        // form the new links
        fast->next = head;
        head = slow->next;
        slow->next = NULL;

        return head;
    }
};
```

