solutions.content:
Intuition: right shift is tricky, but left shift follows the list direction. So, let's rotate list ```len - k``` times left instead.

- Count nodes (len) until we reach the tail.
- Connect head to tail (the list is short-circuited now).
- Then, move head and tail ```len - k``` times.
> Tip: use ```k % len``` to optimize for large ```k```.
- Finally, break the list at tail and return head.
```
ListNode* rotateRight(ListNode* head, int k, int len = 1) {
  for (auto tail = head; tail != nullptr; tail = tail->next, ++len)
    if (tail->next == nullptr) {
      tail->next = head;
      for (k = len - k % len; k > 0; --k) head = head->next, tail = tail->next;
      tail->next = nullptr;
    }
  return head;
}
```

