# **Description:**

🌳 Check out my C++ solution for the "Erect the Fence" problem on LeetCode!
🔍 The challenge is to find the convex hull of a set of points representing trees.
📐 I've implemented the Convex Hull algorithm to solve this problem efficiently.
# **Approach:**

🔄 Sort the given points in ascending order based on their x-coordinate.
🔄 In case of a tie in x-coordinates, sort them based on their y-coordinate.
⏩ This ensures a counter-clockwise order of points, vital for finding the convex hull.
🧭 Use the check() function to determine if a given point is inside the convex hull.
🧭 check() calculates the cross product of three points and checks if it's negative.
🔄 If negative, the third point is outside the convex hull, so pop the last point from the answer list.
📝 The outerTrees() function finds the convex hull using a stack-like approach.
📝 It scans from left to right to find the upper part of the convex hull.
🔄 Then, it reverses the list and scans from right to left to find the lower part.
🎯 This ensures that we have the complete convex hull.
## **Time Complexity:**

⏰ O(n log n) due to the sorting step.
⏰ The stack-like traversal to find the convex hull takes linear time.
# **Conclusion:**

🎉 I hope you find this solution helpful for solving the "Erect the Fence" problem!
💬 Feel free to comment if you have any questions or suggestions for improvement.
🚀 Happy coding and have fun solving LeetCode challenges! 😊
Best regards,
# **VIVEK JAIN**

# Code
